{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2c3a3832-1605-47c0-ba19-c8e771199f58","content":"Here's what you need to change:\n\n**1. Update NuGet packages:**\n- Remove `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`\n- Update `NUnit3TestAdapter` to **v5.0.0+** (it bundles Microsoft.Testing.Platform support)\n- Add `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` if you need TRX output\n\n**2. Add an MSBuild property** in your `.csproj`:\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**3. Add a `Program.cs` entry point** (or use the auto-generated one):\nThe adapter v5+ can auto-generate it. If you need custom config, add:\n```csharp\n<GenerateTestingPlatformEntryPoint>false</GenerateTestingPlatformEntryPoint>\n```\nand write your own.\n\n**4. Run tests with:**\n```bash\ndotnet test         # works with the MSBuild property above\ndotnet run          # also works — the project is now executable\n```\n\n**Key differences to expect:**\n- Each test project compiles to an **executable**, not a DLL\n- `--filter` syntax changes slightly (use `--filter \"Name=MyTest\"`)\n- VSTest `.runsettings` are **not** supported; configure via code or CLI args instead","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"138084d9-73d2-4ea5-a1f4-8879fb95c818","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge question - I don't need to explore a codebase. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":406,"requestId":"1BD0:2DDEB2:2012FD5:23737DA:6A03CE0F"},"id":"2d606c0f-da17-48b8-8feb-1a26ee3a55eb","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:04:27.282Z","parentId":"8c904b68-071f-410b-8281-57679713a581"}
